<topic template="Default" lasteditedby="Liset" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">XS0650</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">XS0650</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Bad array declarator: To declare a managed array the rank specifier precedes the variable&apos;s identifier. To declare a fixed size buffer field, use the fixed keyword before the field type.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">An array was declared incorrectly. In C#, unlike in C and C++, the square brackets follow the type, not the variable name. Also, realize that the syntax for a fixed size buffer differs from that of an array.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2"><text styleclass="Heading2" translate="true">Example</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The following example code generates CS0650.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Code with box"><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">// CS0650.cs &#160;</text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">public class MyClass &#160;</text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">{ &#160;</text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true"> &#160; public static void Main() &#160;</text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true"> &#160; { &#160;</text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">// Generates CS0650. Incorrect array declaration syntax: &#160;</text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true"> &#160; &#160; &#160;int myarray[2]; &#160; &#160; </text><br/><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true"> &#160; &#160; &#160;// Correct declaration. &#160;</text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true"> &#160; &#160; &#160;int[] myarray2; &#160;</text><br/><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true"> &#160; &#160; &#160;// Declaration and initialization in one statement &#160;</text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true"> &#160; &#160; &#160;int[] myArray3= new int[2] {1,2} &#160;</text><br/><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true"> &#160; &#160; &#160;// Access an array element. &#160;</text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true"> &#160; &#160; &#160;myarray3[0] = 0; &#160;</text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true"> &#160; &#160;} &#160;</text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">} &#160;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2"><text styleclass="Heading2" translate="true">Example</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The following example shows how to use the fixed keyword when you create a fixed size buffer:</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Code with box"><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">// This code must appear in an unsafe block. &#160; </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">public struct MyArray &#160; </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">{ &#160;</text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true"> &#160; &#160;public fixed char pathName[128]; &#160;</text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">} &#160;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> &#160;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
  </body>
